    <Callout type="gold">
      <strong>The most common mistake:</strong> Choosing a strategy based on what sounds most exciting rather than what fits your actual resources. SEO sounds appealing because it "works while you sleep" — but it requires 6–12 months of consistent content production before meaningful results. If you need leads in 30 days, SEO is the wrong primary strategy regardless of its long-term potential.
    </Callout>
